Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery lagynos at neck join. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181 27? Name Komos. From the same die as Athens, Agora SS2368.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ID.110)
